The paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach for clustering temporal point processes, which involves modeling the intensity function of the point process using a policy network. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for decomposing the observed sequence into states and actions, which could potentially place it under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves information theory concepts such as entropy and mutual information, which could place it under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations of the proposed method, which could place it under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
